OL,3,CGovernment backed local inquiries into
OL,4,Cgrooming gangs to be announced
OL,6,FTory leader Kemi Badenoch and her
OL,7,Fparty tried to force a vote on the
OL,8,Fissue last Wednesday, but the
OL,9,Famendment to a Labour bill on
OL,10,Fsafeguarding children was
OL,11,Funsurprisingly defeated. If MPs backed
OL,12,Fthe amendment it would've derailed the
OL,13,Fwhole bill.
OL,15,FStarmer hit out at the Conservatives
OL,16,Flast week for not acting on the
OL,17,Frecommendations of the 2022 inquiry,
OL,18,Finsisting "they've been tweeting and
OL,19,Ftalking, we've been acting."
